\c 138
\s1 A psalm written by David
\q1
\v 1 TUHAN, dengan seluruh keberadaanku, aku bersyukur kepada-Mu.
\q1 Aku memuji-Mu di hadapan para dewa palsu untuk merendahkan mereka.
\q1
\v 2 Aku bersujud sementara aku menengadah ke arah Rumah Kudus-Mu,
\q2 dan aku bersyukur karena Engkau mengasihi kami terus menerus dan selalu menepati janji-janji-Mu.
\q2 Engkau sudah membuktikan bahwa penggenapan janji-janji-Mu jauh lebih dahsyat dari apapun juga.
\q1
\v 3 Pada hari aku berseru kepada-Mu, Engkau menjawab aku,
\q2 Engkau membuatku menjadi kuat dan berani.
\b
\q1
\v 4 TUHAN, akan tiba harinya, ketika semua raja-raja di bumi ini memuji Engkau,
\q2 sebab mereka akan mendengar semua perkataan-Mu.
\q1
\v 5 They will sing about what you have done,
\q2 and they will sing and say that you are very great.
\b
\q1
\v 6 Yahweh, you are supreme,
\q2 but you take care of people \add who are considered to be\add* unimportant.
\q1 And you know what proud people \add are doing\add*
\q2 even though they are far away \add from you and think that you do not seethem\add*.
\q1
\v 7 When I am in the midst of many troubles/difficulties,
\q2 you save/rescue me.
\q1 With your hand/power [MTY] you rescue me from my enemies who are angry at me.
\q1
\v 8 Yahweh, you will do for me everything that you promised;
\q2 you faithfully love us forever.
\q2 Finish what you started to do \add for us, your Israeli people\add*!